<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>6 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS INTERNATIONAL MODEL ES52-7A AND ESO65-7A 6-PLUS - DISASSEMBLY - MAINSHAFT
        DISASSEMBLY
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="12">
        <title>MAINSHAFT DISASSEMBLY</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place the shaft in a vise with protected jaws or in a holding fixture,
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300648">Figure 48</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300648" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300648" filename="../figg13/g1300648.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 48. Shaft In a Vise</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the spiral snap ring from the groove. This is accomplished by placing a screwdriver
                under one end and working it around the snap ring,
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300649">Figure 49</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300649" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300649" filename="../figg13/g1300649.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 49. Spiral Snap Ring From Groove</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Attach a suitable puller to the 5th/6th speed clutch gear. Remove the gear and the drive
                gear pocket bearing together,
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300650">Figure 50</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300650" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300650" filename="../figg13/g1300650.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 50. Remove Gear and Drive Gear Pocket Bearing</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1300651">Figure 51</hotlnk>, exploded view of mainshaft assembly.
        </para>
        <figure id="f1300651" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1300651" filename="../figg13/g1300651.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 51. Exploded View of Mainshaft Assembly</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Next remove the overdrive gear in a 13MAH (overdrive) unit, or 5th speed gear in a 13MAG
                (direct drive) unit. There are two caged needle bearings in the gear,
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300652">Figure 52</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300652" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300652" filename="../figg13/g1300652.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 52. Remove Overdrive Gear</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the snap ring, thrust washer, and lock ball. The lock ball (arrow) prevents the
                thrust washer from turning on the shaft. Also remove 4th speed gear, and the two caged needle bear ings,
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300653">Figure 53</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300653" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300653" filename="../figg13/g1300653.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 53. Lock Ball</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the 3rd/4th speed synchronizer from the shaft,
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300654">Figure 54</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300654" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300654" filename="../figg13/g1300654.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 54. 3rd/4th Speed Synchronizer</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the snap ring and 3rd/4th speed clutch gear. Also remove 3rd speed gear and the two
                caged needle bearings. Notice that one bearing is wider than the other. This will be important during
                reassembly. Wider bearing will be toward the rear of mainshaft assembly,
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300655">Figure 55</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300655" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300655" filename="../figg13/g1300655.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 55. Remove 3rd Speed Gear</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">The snap ring, thrust washer, and lock ball (ar row) can be removed. Also remove 2nd speed
                gear and the caged needle bearing,
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300656">Figure 56</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300656" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300656" filename="../figg13/g1300656.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 56. Remove 2nd Speed Gear</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the 1st/2nd speed synchronizer,
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300657">Figure 57</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300657" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300657" filename="../figg13/g1300657.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 57. Remove 1st/2nd Speed Synchronizer</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the mainshaft intermediate bearing us ing a suitable puller as shown,
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300658">Figure 58</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300658" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300658" filename="../figg13/g1300658.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 58. Remove Mainshaft Intermediate Bearing</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Then remove the thrust washer, 1st speed gear, and the caged roller bearing,
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300659">Figure 59</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300659" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300659" filename="../figg13/g1300659.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 59. Remove 1st Speed Gear</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
